Course Goals

    Explain, in depth, benefits of Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform 3

    Identify and qualify use cases

    Explain OpenShift 3 positioning in competitive landscape

    Explain technical architecture

    Demonstrate OpenShift 3
------------------------------------------------------
Module Topics

    Course Goals

    Course Activities

    Course Overview

    Assumptions

    Class Environment

    Connection Details
---------------------------------------------
Course Activities
Selling OpenShift Activity Group

    Describe use of containers

    List four descriptive statements that define what OpenShift is

    Describe in detail benefits of PaaS and OpenShift

    List four OpenShift capabilities that enable DevOps and continuous integration (CI)

    Describe the OpenShift development model (origin → container platform)

    Describe Red Hat OpenShift commercial offerings

    Describe OpenShift Commons

    Describe how companies are changing their development approach

	

    Describe how Red Hat addresses container adoption concerns

    List critical features of OpenShift for Developers and operations

    Describe basic OpenShift security features

    Describe persistent storage and its benefits with OpenShift

    Describe aggregated logging and metrics collection features in OpenShift

    Describe benefits of source-to-image (S2I)

    Describe OpenShift objection handling

    Discover and qualify OpenShift use cases

    Explain Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform positioning in competitive landscape
--------------------------------------------------

Course Activities
OpenShift Architecture Activity Group

    Describe what pods and containers are

    Describe role of masters and infranodes

    Describe role of nodes

    Describe what services and routes are and what they are used for

    Describe external routing into OpenShift applications and role of router

    Describe internal routing within OpenShift

    Describe role of scheduler and replication controllers

    Describe workflow of OpenShift pod deployment

	

    Demonstrate deploying binary container from external registry

    Conduct discussion and whiteboard session of technical architecture of OpenShift deployment

    Describe labels and their role within OpenShift

    Review items in OpenShift web console or the command line: nodes, labels, services, routes, pods, containers

    Provide brief overview of OpenShift aggregated logging and metrics collection facilities

    Demonstrate in-browser (per-pod) and aggregated logging

    Demonstrate collecting load and review metrics
---------------------------------------------------------
Course Activities
OpenShift User Experience Activity Group

    Describe role of projects and users

    Demonstrate user’s view of the OpenShift web console

    Demonstrate project ownership, isolation, and sharing

    Describe role of quotas and limits

    Demonstrate viewing project’s quota and limits using OpenShift web console

    Demonstrate scaling application up to allowed quota

    Describe S2I process

    Describe role of OpenShift integrated registry

    Describe role of build configurations

    Describe role of image stream and images

    Demonstrate creating S2I-based image
---------------------------------------------------
Course Activities
CICD and Pipelines with OpenShift Activity Group

    Describe role of deployment configurations

    Provide brief overview of OpenShift deployment options

    Demonstrate scaling application and triggering new deployment

    Describe CICD workflow and how it is implemented with OpenShift

    Demonstrate delivery pipelines/Jenkins integration and explain the software delivery life cycle (SDLC) and promotion paths

    Demonstrate how using environment variables and internal DNS system wire application components together

    Describe the role of templates

    Demonstrate deploying a multicomponent application from template

    Demonstrate OpenShift integration with Red Hat CloudForms

    Demonstrate using pod/container terminal
------------------------------------------------------
Course Overview
Course Modules

    Introduction to Course and Learning Environment

    OpenShift Architecture

    OpenShift User Experience

    CICD and Pipelines with OpenShift
-------------------------------------------------
Assumptions

    You want to learn how to use Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform

    You can read and modify some form of code

    You have a workstation available for this training

    You have an SSH client installed on your workstation
--------------------------------------
Class Environment

    Shared OpenShift cluster provisioned in Amazon Web Services (AWS) and shared between all OPENTLC users

    Provisioning the environment(s) required for this course is covered in the lab(s) for this module.
